{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015HyeQJxLToDEwJZiMFGF6j","type":"tool_result","content":"MongoDB is already running with TLS. Its current server certificates are nearing\nexpiry. Rotate the server certificates without downtime, keep the existing CA\ntrust unchanged, and ensure the new server certificates are valid for about one year.\n\nNotes:\n- The CA cert and key are stored in the secret mongodb-tls-ca.\n- The current server cert is stored in mongodb-tls-cert.\n- The openssl-toolbox pod is available to generate new certificates.===PRECON===\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n mongodb get pod mongo-rs-0 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n1\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':probe] $ kubectl -n mongodb get secret mongodb-tls-cert\nError from server (NotFound): secrets \"mongodb-tls-cert\" not found\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/resource/services.yaml\nservice/mongo configured\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get pod openssl-toolbox >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/resource/openssl-toolbox.yaml'\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod openssl-toolbox --timeout=300s\npod/openssl-toolbox condition met\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':apply] $ set -e\nTMP_DIR=$(mktemp -d)\nkubectl -n mongodb exec openssl-toolbox -- /bin/sh -c '\nset -e\nmkdir -p /tmp/certs\ncat > /tmp/certs/openssl.cnf <<EOF\ndistinguished_name=req_distinguished_name\nreq_extensions=v3_req\nprompt=no\n[req_distinguished_name]\nCN=mongo-rs\n[v3_req]\nkeyUsage=critical,digitalSignature,keyEncipherment\nextendedKeyUsage=serverAuth,clientAuth\nsubjectAltName=@alt_names\n[alt_names]\nDNS.1=localhost\nDNS.2=mongo\nDNS.3=mongo.mongodb\nDNS.4=mongo.mongodb.svc\nDNS.5=mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.6=mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.7=mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.8=mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nEOF\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/certs/ca.key 2048\nopenssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key /tmp/certs/ca.key -sha256 -days 3650 -subj \"/CN=mongo-ca\" -out /tmp/certs/ca.crt\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/certs/server.key 2048\nopenssl req -new -key /tmp/certs/server.key -out /tmp/certs/server.csr -config /tmp/certs/openssl.cnf\nopenssl x509 -req -in /tmp/certs/server.csr -CA /tmp/certs/ca.crt -CAkey /tmp/certs/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out /tmp/certs/server.crt -days 2 -extensions v3_req -extfile /tmp/certs/openssl.cnf\ncat /tmp/certs/server.crt /tmp/certs/server.key > /tmp/certs/server.pem\n'\nkubectl -n mongodb cp openssl-toolbox:/tmp/certs \"${TMP_DIR}/certs\"\nkubectl -n mongodb create secret generic mongodb-tls-ca \\\n  --from-file=ca.crt=\"${TMP_DIR}/certs/ca.crt\" \\\n  --from-file=ca.key=\"${TMP_DIR}/certs/ca.key\" \\\n  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\nkubectl -n mongodb create secret generic mongodb-tls-cert \\\n  --from-file=server.pem=\"${TMP_DIR}/certs/server.pem\" \\\n  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\nSERVER_FP=$(openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in \"${TMP_DIR}/certs/server.crt\" | cut -d= -f2)\nCA_FP=$(openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in \"${TMP_DIR}/certs/ca.crt\" | cut -d= -f2)\nkubectl -n mongodb create configmap mongodb-tls-old \\\n  --from-literal=server_fingerprint_sha256=\"${SERVER_FP}\" \\\n  --from-literal=ca_fingerprint_sha256=\"${CA_FP}\" \\\n  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n\ntar: removing leading '/' from member names\nsecret/mongodb-tls-ca created\nsecret/mongodb-tls-cert created\nconfigmap/mongodb-tls-old created\nCertificate request self-signature ok\nsubject=CN=mongo-rs\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/resource/statefulset.yaml\nstatefulset.apps/mongo-rs configured\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb rollout status sts mongo-rs --timeout=300s || true\nfor i in $(seq 1 60); do\n  ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts mongo-rs -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n  if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  sleep 5\ndone\nexit 1\n\nWaiting for partitioned roll out to finish: 0 out of 3 new pods have been updated...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for partitioned roll out to finish: 1 out of 3 new pods have been updated...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for partitioned roll out to finish: 2 out of 3 new pods have been updated...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\nWaiting for 1 pods to be ready...\npartitioned roll out complete: 3 new pods have been updated...\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_self_contained:preconditionUnits[1] 'mongo_tls_self_contained':verify] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret mongodb-tls-cert >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n\n\n[precondition:mongo_tls_baseline_capture:preconditionUnits[2] 'mongo_tls_baseline_capture':probe] $ kubectl -n mongodb get configmap mongodb-tls-old\nNAME              DATA   AGE\nmongodb-tls-old   2      65s\n\n===AGENTLOG===\n{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"init\",\"cwd\":\"/mydata/karma/runs/long-rerun/mongodb-long-all-cases-marathon-a-20260618_155709/stages/stage_07\",\"session_id\":\"712f989c-5366-444b-b7bb-1031be4e0285\",\"tools\":[\"Task\",\"AskUserQuestio